{"type":"message","id":"88255817","parentId":"4e697a61","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:30:55.410Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_pOhUf2CfF7Ss9Z9WAv2VY2me","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-09 - Daily Workspace Janitor Scan\n\n## Cron Job Execution\n- **Time**: 2026-03-09 13:03 PM (America/Panama) / 18:03 UTC\n- **Job ID**: f0b88442-8dbd-416d-8444-75c611abac46\n- **Action**: workspace-janitor scan\n\n## Scan Results\n- **Total files scanned**: 548\n- **Total workspace size**: 25.4 MB\n- **Scan completed**: Successfully\n\n## File Classification Summary\n- **SAFE**: 360 files (protected zones, critical risk)\n- **SYSTEM**: 46 files (configuration files, low risk)\n- **TEMPORARY**: 1 file (`temp_watchdog.py`, low risk)\n- **PROJECT_ARTIFACT**: 57 files (project files, medium risk)\n- **MEMORY_BACKUP**: 14 files (backup files, low risk)\n- **UNKNOWN**: 70 files (unclassified, high risk)\n\n## Cleanup Analysis\n- **Cleanup candidates**: 0 files\n- **Reason**: No files have exceeded expiration thresholds\n- **Expiration policies**:\n  - TEMPORARY files: 7 days (current: 3.6 days for `temp_watchdog.py`)\n  - PROJECT_ARTIFACT files: 30 days (all files < 30 days)\n  - MEMORY_BACKUP files: 30 days (all files < 30 days)\n\n## Workspace Health Status\n✅ **HEALTHY** - Workspace is clean and well-maintained\n- All files are within expiration thresholds\n- Protected zones are intact\n- No obsolete files detected\n\n## Recommendations\n1. Continue daily scans via cron job\n2. Monitor `temp_watchdog.py` - will become eligible for cleanup after March 12, 2026\n3. Review UNKNOWN files (70 files) for potential classification or cleanup consideration\n\n## Files Created/Updated\n1. `workspace_inventory.json` - Updated with latest scan (548 files)\n2. `workspace_classification.json` - Updated classification data\n3. `JANITOR_CLEANUP_REPORT.md` - Generated report (0 candidates)\n4. `janitor_log.md` - Log entry added\n\n## Next Scheduled Scan\n- Daily cron job will run again tomorrow\n- Manual scan can be triggered with: `workspace-janitor scan`\n\n---\n\n## Salesforce Skill Hardening Upgrade - COMPLETED SUCCESSFULLY\n\n### Timeline: 2026-03-09 13:25 - 14:22 EST\n### Architect: MAIN agent\n### Status: ✅ ALL PRIORITY IMPROVEMENTS IMPLEMENTED\n\n### 🎯 IMPROVEMENTS IMPLEMENTED:\n\n1. **✅ PARSER ESTRUCTURADO PARA REFERENCIAS** - YAML/JSON\n   - Converted all references to structured YAML format\n   - Files: `role_model.yaml`, `state_machine.yaml`, `dod_definitions.yaml`\n   - Benefits: Deterministic parsing, validatable structure, easy maintenance\n\n2. **✅ MOTOR REAL DE STATE MACHINE** - Robust validation\n   - Created `state_machine_engine.py` with complete validation\n   - Features: State transition validation, automatic state detection, complete history, hard blocking rules, controlled regression handling\n   - Benefits: Architect can properly block/allow by phase, guaranteed consistency\n\n3. **✅ VALIDACIÓN DETERMINÍSTICA DE DoD** - Clear rules\n   - Implemented `dod_validator.py` with deterministic rules\n   - Rules: Mandatory fields by role, minimum sections, required evidence (min 3 pieces), complete handoff, quantitative scoring (0-100%)\n   - Benefits: Objective validation, clear acceptance/rejection criteria, specific feedback\n\n4. **✅ README / PROJECT CONTROL FILE ROBUSTO** - Single source of truth\n   - Developed `project_control.py` with complete system\n   - Features: README.md auto-generated from `.project_control.yaml`, bidirectional sync, complete artifact history, code audit tracking, incident registry\n   - Benefits: Single source of truth, automatic consistent updates, complete project audit\n\n### 🔗 INTEGRATED SYSTEM:\n- **`integrated_hardening.py`**: Unified API combining all 3 components\n- **Workflow**: Creation → Validation → Registration → Reporting\n- **Health metrics**: Quantitative project health score (0-100%)\n\n### 📊 TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE:\n```\nStructured references (YAML) → Validation engines → Integrated system → Project control\n```\n\n### 🎯 OBJECTIVES ACHIEVED:\n- ✅ `salesforce-architect` as single governing skill\n- ✅ Hardened project routing discipline\n- ✅ Formalized role templates (once, in YAML)\n- ✅ Formal project state machine with real engine\n- ✅ Role-based Definition of Done with deterministic validation\n- ✅ Hardened architect ↔ auditor integration\n- ✅ Sub-agents as default execution model\n- ✅ Avoid persistent agent sprawl\n- ✅ Preserve existing working pipelines and artifacts\n\n\n[405 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773099055406}}
