{"type":"message","id":"0d3f70b5","parentId":"2234dd51","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:32:45.342Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes! The issue is in `analyze_daily_notes`. It's taking the raw line from the daily note and prepending the date: `events.append(f\"{date}: {line.strip()}\")`. If the line already has a `- ` prefix (like `- **Scan completed**: Successfully`), then the event becomes `\"2026-03-09: - **Scan completed**: Successfully\"`.\n\nThen in `update_memory_sections`, it adds another `- ` prefix: `new_milestones.append(f\"- {event}\")`, resulting in `\"- 2026-03-09: - **Scan completed**: Successfully\"`.\n\nBut wait, that's not the only issue! The `if event not in milestone_lines:` check compares the new event (which has the date prepended) with existing milestone lines (which are just the bullet points without checking if they already have that date). So even if the milestone already exists in MEMORY.md, it won't be recognized as a duplicate because the comparison is wrong.\n\nActually, let me check what the existing milestone lines in MEMORY.md look like:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6H0RnCaYC7WkYefLS99OK7F5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"^- \" ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":577,"output":292,"cacheRead":33024,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773099155359}}
